{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ec182b1d-3221-4992-be1f-3d8572c87f37","content":"In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. You override `CreateWindow` in your `App` class and use a custom `Window`:\n\n```csharp\npublic partial class App : Application\n{\n    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    {\n        var window = new Window(new AppShell());\n\n        window.Created += (s, e) => { /* OnStart equivalent */ };\n        window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* OnResume equivalent */ };\n        window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep equivalent */ };\n\n        return window;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAlternatively, subclass `Window` and override `OnCreated()`, `OnResumed()`, and `OnStopped()`/`OnBackgrounding()` directly.\n\nKey mapping:\n| Xamarin.Forms | .NET MAUI Window |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart` | `Created` / `OnCreated()` |\n| `OnSleep` | `Stopped` / `OnStopped()` |\n| `OnResume` | `Resumed` / `OnResumed()` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7059ceb6-acfc-425f-b84e-4a77e17315ab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI, specifically about the lifecycle methods OnStart, OnSleep, and OnResume that were overridden in the Application class.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. Instead of overriding those methods directly on the Application class, MAUI uses a cross-platform lifecycle events system through the `Window` class or by hooking into platform-specific lifecycle events via the `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` method, or by using the `Window` lifecycle events.\n\nActually, let me be more precise:\n\n1. In .NET MAUI, the `Application` class still exists but `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` are no longer virtual methods you override directly on `Application`.\n\n\n2. Instead, I can hook into the `Window` lifecycle events like `Created`, `Stopped`, and `Resumed`, or I can create a custom `Window` class by overriding `Application.CreateWindow()` and implementing the corresponding lifecycle methods there.","outputTokens":635,"requestId":"A421:30E8DC:5F532EC:67C9665:69F00560"},"id":"cebd5fd3-faf8-41c9-a0f8-e520c79d1ce8","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:08.054Z","parentId":"0780930e-c954-497f-adee-ed07a2f308cf"}
